1. Clone the repo:


git clone git@github.com:Ten-One-Zero-Three/devconnect.git
cd devconnect/web103_finalproject
2. Create your .env file in server/:


PORT=
PGDATABASE=
PGHOST=
PGPASSWORD=
PGPORT=5432
PGUSER=
(Ask An for the credentials — never share in chat)

3. Install dependencies:


cd server && npm install
cd ../client && npm install
4. Always work on a branch, never on main:


git checkout -b feature/your-feature-name
5. Commit and push your branch:


git add .
git commit -m "what you did"
git push -u origin feature/your-feature-name
6. Open a Pull Request on GitHub — An will review and merge it.

Send them the credentials privately (Slack/DM), not in the repo.